Butt (Broadcast using this tool) is an awesome cross-platform tool that I use for streaming my radio show.
	There are two ways to install it in linux:

	1. The source way. Download Butt and untar it.
		+cd <buttdirectoy>+
		+./configure+
		+make+
		+make install+
	See butt READ ME file for a list of all required depedency.

	2. The CLI way
		Add the epel repo:
			+yum install epel-release+
		Add the Nux Desktop repo:
			+yum install http://li.nux.ro/download/nux/dextop/el7/x86_64/nux-dextop-release-0-5.el7.nux.noarch.rpm+

		Add RABE APEL repo:
	
		+curl -o /etc/yum.repos.d/home:radiorabe:audio.repo \
     http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/radiorabe:/audio/CentOS_7/home:radiorabe:audio.repo+

		Add RABE Streambox repo:
		+curl -o /etc/yum.repos.d/home:radiorabe:streambox.repo \
     http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/radiorabe:/streambox/CentOS_7/home:radiorabe:streambox.repo+

Then you're ready to install butt: +yum install butt+


 
